ing ideas (teamwork), egocentric (contradicts concern for others?), not willing to further education (development). Mixed.\n\nD: strengths: responds adequately to unexpected events (calmness), concentration, problem solving, takes responsibility seriously (reliability). Weaknesses: moody, loner (teamwork). Adequate but not outstanding.\n\nThus B seems strongest overall: reliability, calm, technical, but communication tone issue. D also reliable and responsible but moody and loner may be problematic for crew. C has good decision-making and concern for others but communication difficulty and egocentric may be problematic. A lacks reliability and calmness, plus unfriendly and unhealthy.\n\nThus likely B is best. But we should ask other agents for any missing info about other candidates, maybe about D's calmness or C's reliability, etc. However we have enough to make a vote. But we should also consider that we need to weigh strengths and weaknesses holistically. B's pretentiousness and tone issues could be mitigated? But we cannot mitigate; we must weigh as evidence. Still B's reliability and calmness are critical for long-distance flights. The communication tone issue could be a problem but maybe less severe than lack of reliability.\n\nThus I will vote for Candidate B.\n\nWe should also maybe ask Agent 2 about Candidate D's reliability or calmness? But we have D's reliability: takes responsibility seriously, but no explicit reliability rating. Could ask for more about D's reliability. But time limited. I think we can vote.\n\nPublic message: summarize evaluation and vote."}
