antified); A and C \u2013 no explicit data.\n- **Calmness under pressure:** B (keeps calm in crisis); D (responds adequately); C (handles stress very well); A \u2013 no data.\n- **Technical competence:** All have strengths, but B\u2019s weather\u2011assessment and computer\u2011skill expertise are directly relevant to long\u2011haul flight planning.\n- **Teamwork/communication:** B\u2019s pretentiousness and tone issues are noted, yet they appear less severe than C\u2019s communication difficulty/egocentrism, D\u2019s hot\u2011tempered loner attitude, or A\u2019s poor reception of criticism.\nGiven the paramount importance of reliability and calmness for international, high\u2011responsibility flights, **Candidate\u202fB** remains the most compelling overall choice. The communication\u2011style concerns, while relevant, are less critical than the lack of reliability or composure evidence for the other candidates.\nTherefore, I continue to support **Candidate\u202fB** for the long\u2011distance pilot position.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We are agent_3. We have just used tool agent_1_tool to get info, which matches what we already know. Now we need to produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with our vote. We have all info now. We need to evaluate and possibly ask further questions if any missing info. We have reliability for A unknown, calmness for A unknown, reliability for C unknown, calmness for C supported by \"handles stress very well\", reliability for D supported by \"takes responsibility seriously\". Also we have other attributes for each candidate from earlier. We need to decide final vote. All agents currently favor B. We should consider if any new info could change that. B still strongest: reliability 100%, calmness, technical, some communication issues. D has reliability and calmness but teamwork issues. C has calmness but no reliability. A lacks both. So B remains best. We should also maybe ask about any missing info that could affect: maybe ask about candidate D's calmness more specifically? But we have \"responds to unexpected events adequately\" which is some calmness. Could ask about candidate A's calmness? No info. Could ask about candidate C's reliability? No info. Since we have no further info, we can finalize vote for B. Also we could ask other agents if they have any info on candidate C reliability or candidate A calmness, but we already asked agent_1 and got no info. Could ask agent_2? But we already asked earlier and they said no. So we can just finalize.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE summarizing evaluation, note missing info, reaffirm vote for B. Then METADATA_JSON with vote B."}
